> Thnx Gerald, for the sites.  The site describing the f*rd bronco fuel
> pump inertia switch is complete with pics on how it works.  It would
> seem that this type of switch would be the ultimate solution for
> electric fuel pumps in retrofitted busses.  I know there must be a lot
> of these out there because f*rd bronco's rust out badly up here.
> Stan Skelton in Kimberley

Don't forget the $99 switch: install a n/o relay inline with the oil
pressure switch light and use that to trigger the fuel pump using the other
terminals. You have to crank the engine to build a little oil pressure first
but it also shuts off the pump when the engine dies.

